{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781544953515,"sessionID":"ses_133a82fbbffevAjtqNLJ4lglcd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_Wd5LBHdGLWlJSkyXnRPO1SAK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"open.?design|open_design|chrome_devtools|clickup|figma","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.utcp_config.json","include":"*.json"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.utcp_config.json:\n  Line 16:       \"name\": \"chrome_devtools_1\",\n\n  Line 20:           \"chrome_devtools_1\": {\n\n  Line 33:       \"name\": \"chrome_devtools_2\",\n\n  Line 37:           \"chrome_devtools_2\": {\n\n  Line 50:       \"name\": \"clickup_official\",\n\n  Line 54:           \"clickup_official\": {\n\n  Line 59:               \"@clickup/mcp-server\"\n\n  Line 70:       \"name\": \"figma\",\n\n  Line 74:           \"figma\": {\n\n  Line 79:               \"figma-developer-mcp@latest\",\n\n  Line 127:       \"name\": \"open_design\",\n\n  Line 131:           \"open_design\": {\n\n  Line 140:               \"OD_SIDECAR_IPC_PATH\": \"/tmp/open-design/ipc/release-stable/daemon.sock\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/graph-metadata.json:\n  Line 9:     \"skilled-agent-orchestration/053-cli-skill-removal-mcp-clickup\",\n\n  Line 23:     \"skilled-agent-orchestration/067-mcp-figma-transfer\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/150-mcp-open-design/008-mcp-magicpath-deprecation/description.json:\n  Line 3:   \"specFolder\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/150-mcp-open-design/008-mcp-magicpath-deprecation\",\n\n  Line 16:     \"150-mcp-open-design\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/150-mcp-open-design/008-mcp-magicpath-deprecation/graph-metadata.json:\n  Line 3:   \"packet_id\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/150-mcp-open-design/008-mcp-magicpath-deprecation\",\n\n  Line 4:   \"spec_folder\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/150-mcp-open-design/008-mcp-magicpath-deprecation\",\n\n  Line 5:   \"parent_id\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/150-mcp-open-design\",\n\n  Line 18:       \"magicpath superseded by open design\",\n\n  Line 19:       \"re-center design protocol on mcp-open-design\",\n\n  Line 40:       \"mcp-open-design\",\n\n  Line 61:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/SKILL.md\",\n\n  Line 62:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/README.md\",\n\n  Line 63:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/graph-metadata.json\",\n\n  Line 64:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md\",\n\n  Line 65:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/SKILL.md\"\n\n  Line 143:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md\",\n\n  Line 213:     \"causal_summary\": \"The `mcp-magicpath` skill drives the hosted MagicPath canvas through the `magicpath-ai` CLI. Spec 150 built `mcp-open-design`, which drives the installed Open Design desktop app from the terminal. That skill was live-verified in phase 004 and corrected to the real multi-turn flow in phase 007. With a terminal-native design transport now in place, `mcp-magicpath` is superseded. Leaving it live splits the shared design protocol across two transports and leaves stale sibling edges and references pointing at a tool the system no longer routes to.\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization/graph-metadata.json:\n  Line 16:       \"mcp-open-design install guide\",\n\n  Line 18:       \"mcp-figma 1.0.0.0\",\n\n  Line 34:       \"mcp-open-design\",\n\n  Line 38:       \"mcp-figma\",\n\n  Line 45:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md\",\n\n  Line 46:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/INSTALL_GUIDE.md\",\n\n  Line 51:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/mcp-servers/open-design/README.md\",\n\n  Line 68:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md\",\n\n  Line 74:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/INSTALL_GUIDE.md\",\n\n  Line 92:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/mcp-servers/open-design/README.md\",\n\n  Line 204:     \"causal_summary\": \"The five mcp-* skills had drifted out of a shared shape. mcp-figma was still labelled pre-1.0 (`0.1.0`) even though its CLI was live-verified and an embedded install scaffold was added. mcp-open-design had no INSTALL_GUIDE and no `scripts/` at all, so it could not be installed or diagnosed like its siblings. mcp-chrome-devtools and mcp-click-up had an `install.sh` but no read-only `doctor.sh`. The central `/doctor:mcp` command knew only the registered MCP servers, so the CLI-primary design skills were invisible to it. Finally, the three design skills (mcp-figma, mcp-open-design, sk-interface-design) referenced each other only partially.\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/150-mcp-open-design/006-sk-prompt-design-tool-usecases/description.json:\n  Line 3:   \"specFolder\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/150-mcp-open-design/006-sk-prompt-design-tool-usecases\",\n\n  Line 19:     \"150-mcp-open-design\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support/review/session-audit/lineages/mimo-v25-pro/deep-review-config.json:\n  Line 2:   \"topic\": \"Review of mcp-figma skill with direct CLI support â€” spec folder 151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support\",\n\n  Line 4:   \"reviewTarget\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support\",\n\n  Line 23:   \"specFolder\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/150-mcp-open-design/006-sk-prompt-design-tool-usecases/graph-metadata.json:\n  Line 3:   \"packet_id\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/150-mcp-open-design/006-sk-prompt-design-tool-usecases\",\n\n  Line 4:   \"spec_folder\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/150-mcp-open-design/006-sk-prompt-design-tool-usecases\",\n\n  Line 5:   \"parent_id\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/150-mcp-open-design\",\n\n  Line 18:       \"sk-prompt magicpath open-design\",\n\n  Line 38:       \"open-design\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/graph-metadata.json:\n  Line 3:   \"skill_id\": \"mcp-open-design\",\n\n  Line 23:         \"target\": \"mcp-figma\",\n\n  Line 37:       \"mcp-figma\"\n\n  Line 46:     \"open-design\"\n\n  Line 49:     \"open design\",\n\n  Line 50:     \"open-design\",\n\n  Line 53:     \"design system from open design\",\n\n  Line 54:     \"drive open design from the terminal\",\n\n  Line 60:       \"open design\",\n\n  Line 61:       \"open-design\",\n\n  Line 64:       \"design system from open design\",\n\n  Line 65:       \"drive open design from the terminal\"\n\n  Line 79:       \"open design\",\n\n  Line 89:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/SKILL.md\",\n\n  Line 90:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/README.md\",\n\n  Line 91:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/od_cli_reference.md\",\n\n  Line 92:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/mcp_wiring.md\",\n\n  Line 93:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/tool_surface.md\",\n\n  Line 94:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md\",\n\n  Line 95:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\",\n\n  Line 96:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md\",\n\n  Line 97:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md\",\n\n  Line 98:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md\"\n\n  Line 102:         \"name\": \"mcp-open-design\",\n\n  Line 104:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/SKILL.md\",\n\n  Line 110:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/README.md\",\n\n  Line 116:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/od_cli_reference.md\",\n\n  Line 122:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/mcp_wiring.md\",\n\n  Line 128:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/tool_surface.md\",\n\n  Line 132:     \"causal_summary\": \"mcp-open-design teaches a terminal agent (opencode or Claude Code) to drive the installed Open Design desktop app through its od CLI and stdio MCP server instead of the in-app chat. Wire with od mcp install, then read local projects and design-systems, reuse them, or commission gated headless runs. Generation is multi-turn: start_run (or od run start) fires turn 1, which returns a discovery question-form with zero files, and the design is built only after od ui respond answers the form. od artifacts create only adds a file, never a rendered design. The od CLI is daemon-cli.mjs run under Node (not the bundled vela auth client) and the daemon is socket-discovered on an ephemeral port (not a fixed 7456), hosted by the desktop app, which also exposes an HTTP API whose port rotates on restart (rediscover via /api/mcp/install-info). Pairs with sk-interface-design (the design judgment) over the shared claude_design_parity loop, and never vendors Open Design content.\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support/review/session-audit/lineages/mimo-v25-pro/deep-review-findings-registry.json:\n  Line 6:     {\"findingId\":\"F001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"category\":\"correctness\",\"status\":\"active\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"title\":\"connect-yolo.sh does not verify Figma Desktop is running before patching\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/scripts/connect-yolo.sh\",\"line\":30,\"firstSeen\":1,\"lastSeen\":1,\"transitions\":[{\"iteration\":1,\"from\":null,\"to\":\"P1\",\"reason\":\"Initial discovery\"}]},\n\n  Line 7:     {\"findingId\":\"F002\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"category\":\"correctness\",\"status\":\"active\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"title\":\"install.sh auto mode does not handle repo install failure gracefully\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/scripts/install.sh\",\"line\":146,\"firstSeen\":1,\"lastSeen\":1,\"transitions\":[{\"iteration\":1,\"from\":null,\"to\":\"P1\",\"reason\":\"Initial discovery\"}]},\n\n  Line 8:     {\"findingId\":\"F003\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"category\":\"correctness\",\"status\":\"active\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"title\":\"Inconsistent daemon file path naming between token and PID\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/scripts/_common.sh\",\"line\":48,\"firstSeen\":1,\"lastSeen\":1,\"transitions\":[{\"iteration\":1,\"from\":null,\"to\":\"P2\",\"reason\":\"Initial discovery\"}]},\n\n  Line 9:     {\"findingId\":\"F004\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"category\":\"correctness\",\"status\":\"active\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"title\":\"tool_surface.md references nonexistent research output file\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/tool_surface.md\",\"line\":164,\"firstSeen\":1,\"lastSeen\":1,\"transitions\":[{\"iteration\":1,\"from\":null,\"to\":\"P2\",\"reason\":\"Initial discovery\"}]},\n\n  Line 10:     {\"findingId\":\"F005\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"category\":\"traceability\",\"status\":\"active\",\"dimension\":\"traceability\",\"title\":\"Graph metadata siblings missing mcp-magicpath edge\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/graph-metadata.json\",\"line\":26,\"firstSeen\":1,\"lastSeen\":1,\"transitions\":[{\"iteration\":1,\"from\":null,\"to\":\"P2\",\"reas