{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781544988204,"sessionID":"ses_133a82fbbffevAjtqNLJ4lglcd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_7qRBtnM51JEdlklToGCo1SRZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"utcp|\\.utcp_config|doctor|open_design|open-design","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization/scratch/brief-open-design-scripts.md:\n  Line 4: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization\n\n  Line 17: - .opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/scripts/_common.sh\n\n  Line 18: - .opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/scripts/install.sh\n\n  Line 19: - .opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/scripts/doctor.sh\n\n  Line 24: - .opencode/skills/mcp-figma/scripts/doctor.sh    (TEMPLATE for doctor.sh: read-only, report-only, never prints secrets)\n\n  Line 25: - .opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/SKILL.md        (the od CLI + daemon + socket facts; read sections \"HOW IT WORKS\", Prerequisites, Rules)\n\n  Line 26: - .opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/references/od_cli_reference.md   (locating the CLI, the daemon/socket model, the od verb surface)\n\n  Line 35:   OD_SOCKET = \"/tmp/open-design/ipc/release-stable/daemon.sock\"\n\n  Line 49:    - Constants: `OD_SOCKET=\"/tmp/open-design/ipc/release-stable/daemon.sock\"`.\n\n  Line 58:    - report_next_steps: 1) open the Open Design desktop app, 2) PREVIEW MCP wiring with `node \"$OD_BIN\" mcp install opencode --print --json` (writes nothing) and review before wiring, 3) run doctor.sh for diagnostics. Make clear install.sh itself wires nothing.\n\n  Line 61: C) scripts/doctor.sh  (read-only diagnostics, report-only)\n\n  Line 63:    - Checks (report-only): platform; Node >= 18; Open Design.app presence; od CLI (daemon-cli.mjs) locatable via od_bin(); `node \"$OD_BIN\" --version`; daemon socket present at OD_SOCKET; desktop app running (`pgrep -f \"Open Design\"` best-effort); whether an \"open-design\" MCP entry is present in `~/.config/opencode/opencode.json` (grep for \"open-design\", report presence only) and best-effort `claude mcp list 2>/dev/null | grep -qi open-design` if `claude` is on PATH.\n\n  Line 64:    - Explicitly note in an info line that the daemon HTTP port is ephemeral, so this doctor does not probe a fixed port.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization/plan.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Implementation Plan: Standardize the mcp-* skills into the install-guide and doctor system\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Bring all five mcp-* skills to a shared install-and-doctor shape and cross-reference the three design skills. Implemented with parallel gpt-5.5-fast write seats for the templated chunks and the orchestrator for the knowledge-heavy chunks.\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"doctor.sh implementation\"\n\n  Line 13:     packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization\"\n\n  Line 20:       - \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/scripts/install.sh\"\n\n  Line 21:       - \".opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_install.yaml\"\n\n  Line 24:       session_id: \"session-153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization\"\n\n  Line 31: # Implementation Plan: Standardize the mcp-* skills into the install-guide and doctor system\n\n  Line 50: Each mcp-* skill is brought to the same surface that mcp-figma already had: an INSTALL_GUIDE.md, a verify-only `scripts/install.sh`, and a read-only `scripts/doctor.sh` whose helper shape mirrors `mcp-figma/scripts/_common.sh`. The central `/doctor:mcp` install asset gains a `cli_skill_diagnostics:` class so the CLI-primary skills are part of the doctor setup without being treated as registered servers. The three design skills are cross-linked in prose and in the skill graph.\n\n  Line 75: Shared skill convention. Each skill's scripts follow the mcp-figma reference shape (`_common.sh` helpers, `install.sh` detect-and-verify, `doctor.sh` read-only report).\n\n  Line 78: - **Per-skill scripts**: `install.sh` (non-mutating) and `doctor.sh` (read-only) per skill.\n\n  Line 79: - **Central doctor class**: `cli_skill_diagnostics:` in `doctor_mcp_install.yaml`, separate from `servers:`.\n\n  Line 80: - **Cross-reference graph**: reciprocal edges among mcp-figma, mcp-open-design, sk-interface-design.\n\n  Line 83: `doctor.sh` reads local state (PATH, app paths, sockets, config files) and prints a report. `install.sh` detects the tool or app, verifies it, and prints gated next steps. Nothing mutates state.\n\n  Line 91: Not a bug fix, but `doctor_mcp_install.yaml` and `mcp.md` are shared command-policy surfaces, so the change is recorded here.\n\n  Line 95: | `doctor_mcp_install.yaml` `servers:` loop | Drives install/repair of registered MCP servers | unchanged | `python3 -c yaml.safe_load` parses; loop still iterates `servers:` only |\n\n  Line 96: | `doctor_mcp_install.yaml` `cli_skill_diagnostics:` | New reference class for CLI-primary skills | added (additive, not consumed by the server loop) | grep shows the four skills; YAML parses |\n\n  Line 97: | `mcp.md` Routing Rules | Documents `/doctor:mcp` scope | update (one rule clarifying the CLI-skill class) | grep shows the new rule |\n\n  Line 98: | per-skill `scripts/doctor.sh` consumers | The operator or agent runs them directly | added | `bash -n` per file; manual read |\n\n  Line 101: - Same-class producers: `rg -n 'doctor.sh|install.sh' .opencode/skills/mcp-*` confirms every mcp skill's script surface.\n\n  Line 102: - Consumers of changed symbols: `rg -n 'cli_skill_diagnostics' .opencode/commands/doctor` confirms only additive references.\n\n  Line 117: - [x] mcp-open-design parity: INSTALL_GUIDE plus scripts (scripts via gpt-5.5 seat, guide by orchestrator)\n\n  Line 118: - [x] doctor.sh for mcp-chrome-devtools and mcp-click-up (gpt-5.5 seats)\n\n  Line 119: - [x] Central doctor `cli_skill_diagnostics:` wiring and mcp.md note\n\n  Line 158: - **Trigger**: A new doctor or install script misbehaves, or the doctor YAML fails to parse.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization/checklist.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Verification Checklist: Standardize the mcp-* skills into the install-guide and doctor system\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"doctor.sh verification\"\n\n  Line 11:     packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization\"\n\n  Line 18:       - \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/scripts/doctor.sh\"\n\n  Line 21:       session_id: \"session-153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization\"\n\n  Line 28: # Verification Checklist: Standardize the mcp-* skills into the install-guide and doctor system\n\n  Line 60: - [x] CHK-011 [P0] No fatal errors (package_skill PASS; one soft open-design 3003/3000-word warning noted)\n\n  Line 61: - [x] CHK-012 [P1] Error handling: doctors warn/info and exit 0 when tools or apps are absent\n\n  Line 83: - [x] CHK-FIX-003 [P0] Consumer check done for the one shared surface (doctor YAML loop iterates `servers:` only; `cli_skill_diagnostics:` is additive)\n\n  Line 107: - [x] CHK-042 [P2] READMEs and INSTALL_GUIDEs updated (cross-refs plus the new open-design guide)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization/spec.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Feature Specification: Standardize the mcp-* skills into the install-guide and doctor system\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"The mcp-* skills were inconsistent: mcp-figma sat at a pre-1.0 version after live verification, mcp-open-design had no INSTALL_GUIDE or install/doctor scripts, two skills lacked a read-only doctor, and the three design skills did not cross-reference each other consistently. This packet standardizes all of them.\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"doctor.sh for mcp skills\"\n\n  Line 7:   - \"mcp-open-design install guide\"\n\n  Line 14:     packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization\"\n\n  Line 17:     recent_action: \"Implemented all skill changes, doctor wiring, and cross-refs; verifying\"\n\n  Line 22:       - \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/INSTALL_GUIDE.md\"\n\n  Line 23:       - \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/scripts/install.sh\"\n\n  Line 24:       - \".opencode/skills/mcp-chrome-devtools/scripts/doctor.sh\"\n\n  Line 25:       - \".opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_install.yaml\"\n\n  Line 28:       session_id: \"session-153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization\"\n\n  Line 36: # Feature Specification: Standardize the mcp-* skills into the install-guide and doctor system\n\n  Line 60: The five mcp-* skills had drifted out of a shared shape. mcp-figma was still labelled pre-1.0 (`0.1.0`) even though its CLI was live-verified and an embedded install scaffold was added. mcp-open-design had no INSTALL_GUIDE and no `scripts/` at all, so it could not be installed or diagnosed like its siblings. mcp-chrome-devtools and mcp-click-up had an `install.sh` but no read-only `doctor.sh`. The central `/doctor:mcp` command knew only the registered MCP servers, so the CLI-primary design skills were invisible to it. Finally, the three design skills (mcp-figma, mcp-open-design, sk-interface-design) referenced each other only partially.\n\n  Line 63: Every mcp-* skill ships the same install-and-doctor surface and is reachable from the central doctor command, and the three design skills cross-reference each other consistently in prose and in the skill graph.\n\n  Line 73: - Bring mcp-open-design to install/doctor parity: a new INSTALL_GUIDE.md and `scripts/{_common.sh, install.sh, doctor.sh}`.\n\n  Line 74: - Add a read-only `scripts/doctor.sh` to mcp-chrome-devtools and mcp-click-up.\n\n  Line 75: - Wire all mcp skills into the central `/doctor:mcp` setup, adding a `cli_skill_diagnostics:` reference class for the CLI-primary skills.\n\n  Line 76: - Make mcp-figma, mcp-open-design, and sk-interface-design cross-reference each other in README, SKILL.md, graph-metadata, and the repo READMEs.\n\n  Line 77: - Add the open-design `mcp-servers/` pointer doc so its layout matches the embedded-server skills.\n\n  Line 81: - Bumping mcp-open-design, mcp-chrome-devtools, or mcp-click-up versions - only mcp-figma was promoted.\n\n  Line 90: | `.opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/INSTALL_GUIDE.md` | Create | New install guide matching the shared standard |\n\n  Line 91: | `.opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/scripts/{_common.sh,install.sh,doctor.sh}` | Create | Install (verify-only) and read-only doctor for the bundled od CLI |\n\n  Line 92: | `.opencode/skills/mcp-chrome-devtools/scripts/doctor.sh` | Create | Read-only diagnostic for the bdg CLI |\n\n  Line 93: | `.opencode/skills/mcp-click-up/scripts/doctor.sh` | Create | Read-only diagnostic for the cupt CLI |\n\n  Line 94: | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_install.yaml` | Modify | Add `cli_skill_diagnostics:` reference class |\n\n  Line 95: | `.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md` | Modify | Document the CLI-skill diagnostic class |\n\n  Line 96: | `.opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/{README.md,SKILL.md}` | Modify | Cross-reference mcp-figma |\n\n  Line 98: | `.opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/mcp-servers/open-design/README.md` | Create | Pointer doc for the bundled CLI and MCP |\n\n  Line 111: | REQ-002 | mcp-open-design install/doctor parity | INSTALL_GUIDE.md plus `scripts/{_common.sh,install.sh,doctor.sh}` exist; `bash -n` passes; install.sh wires nothing and doctor.sh changes nothing |\n\n  Line 112: | REQ-003 | doctor.sh for mcp-chrome-devtools and mcp-click-up | Both files exist, `bash -n` passes, and each checks its real CLI (bdg, cupt) read-only |\n\n  Line 118: | REQ-004 | All mcp skills part of the central doctor setup | `doctor_mcp_install.yaml` lists the 4 CLI-primary skills under `cli_skill_diagnostics:`; mcp.md documents the class; YAML still parses |\n\n  Line 119: | REQ-005 | Three design skills cross-reference each other | Each of mcp-figma, mcp-open-design, sk-interface-design names the other two in its Related section; graph edges are reciprocal |\n\n  Line 120: | REQ-006 | Embedded server layout consistency | mcp-figma `mcp-servers/{figma-cli,figma-mcp}` and mcp-open-design `mcp-servers/open-design` pointer docs exist, mirroring mcp-click-up |\n\n  Line 128: - **SC-001**: All five mcp-* skills have an INSTALL_GUIDE.md, an install.sh, and a read-only doctor.sh (or are correctly classed as a registered server).\n\n  Line 129: - **SC-002**: The central `/doctor:mcp` setup enumerates every mcp skill, with CLI-primary skills in a distinct, non-server class.\n\n  Line 130: - **SC-003**: mcp-figma, mcp-open-design, and sk-interface-design mutually cross-reference each other in prose and in the skill graph.\n\n  Line 137: - **Given** the mcp-chrome-devtools doctor, **When** it runs, **Then** it reports the bdg CLI and Chrome presence read-only and exits 0.\n\n  Line 138: - **Given** the click-up doctor, **When** the `clickup_official` manual is registered, **Then** it reports the ClickUp manual as present.\n\n  Line 139: - **Given** the central doctor YAML, **When** parsed, **Then** `cli_skill_diagnostics:` lists the four CLI-primary skills beside the `servers:` block.\n\n  Line 140: - **Given** sk-interface-design, **When** reading its Related section and graph edges, **Then** both mcp-figma and mcp-open-design appear.\n\n  Line 151: | Risk | gpt-5.5 hallucinating CLI facts | Wrong binary names in doctors | Baked exact facts into briefs and host-verified every generated script against the real install.sh |\n\n  Line 166: - **NFR-P01**: Each doctor.sh completes quickly and never blocks on network or daemon calls (best-effort local probes only).\n\n  Line 170: - **NFR-S02**: install.sh and doctor.sh are non-mutating: they never connect, patch, wire MCP, start a daemon, or pipe a remote installer to a shell.\n\n  Line 173: - **NFR-R01**: doctor.sh degrades gracefully when a tool, app, or browser is absent (warn or info, never a fatal crash) and exits 0.\n\n  Line 183: - Empty input: doctor.sh takes no arguments and runs the full read-only report.\n\n  Line 204: | Scope | 14/25 | ~12 files across 5 skills plus the doctor command, mostly additive docs and scripts |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Implementation Summary: mcp-* skill install and doctor standardization\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"All five mcp-* skills now share one install-and-doctor surface, the central doctor command enumerates every mcp skill, and the three design skills cross-reference each other in prose and in the skill graph.\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"doctor.sh rollout\"\n\n  Line 12:     packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/153-mcp-skill-install-doctor-standardization\"\n\n  Line 20:       - \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/INSTALL_GUIDE.md\"\n\n  Line 21:       - \".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/scripts/doctor.sh\"\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"utcp|\\.utcp_config|doctor|open_design|open-design","time":{"start":1781544988190,"end":1781544988203}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_017abe3f9551e1dc016a30381c097c8191966fc2cc06624837"}},"id":"prt_ecc5b2de7001K9ZvxcWPV4Zw49","sessionID":"ses_133a82fbbffevAjtqNLJ4lglcd","messageID":"msg_ecc5aa91f001SBz2v2GV8VOCHz"}}
