{"type":"text","timestamp":1781545019040,"sessionID":"ses_133a82fbbffevAjtqNLJ4lglcd","part":{"id":"prt_ecc5b95c1001DK2EPdINEeWkNH","messageID":"msg_ecc5b30b90018TjGqSxP4IjFt7","sessionID":"ses_133a82fbbffevAjtqNLJ4lglcd","type":"text","text":"{\"seat\":\"G2\",\"slice\":\"153 utcp-depth + set-e graceful-degradation\",\"findings\":[{\"id\":\"G2-1\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"packet\":\"153\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/mcp-open-design/scripts/doctor.sh\",\"line\":\"75-95\",\"title\":\"mcp-open-design doctor does not check repo .utcp_config.json at all\",\"evidence\":\"Lines 75-95 enter \\\"-- MCP config presence --\\\" but only set `OPENCODE_CONFIG=\\\"$HOME/.config/opencode/opencode.json\\\"`, grep that file for `open-design`, and run `claude mcp list ... | grep -qi 'open-design'`; there is no `UTCP=\\\"$HERE/../../../../.utcp_config.json\\\"` or `.utcp_config.json` probe. The repo root `.utcp_config.json` exists and contains `\\\"name\\\": \\\"open_design\\\"` at line 127.\",\"why\":\"The three other checked doctors live at `.opencode/skills/<skill>/scripts/`, where `../../../../.utcp_config.json` resolves to the repo root correctly. Open Design lives at the same depth, but because it has no UTCP probe, it cannot report the existing Code Mode `open_design` manual and can mask a real registration as absent from its doctor output.\",\"fix\":\"Add the same repo-root UTCP probe in mcp-open-design doctor with `UTCP=\\\"$HERE/../../../../.utcp_config.json\\\"`, guard it with `[ -f \\\"$UTCP\\\" ]` and `if grep ...; then ...; else info ...; fi`, and grep for the actual manual name `open_design`.\"}]}","time":{"start":1781545014721,"end":1781545019036},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0b6c2a85c6fba359016a303836af0c819186a762411be4f0b5","phase":"final_answer"}}}}
